</para><para id="eip-945">“Melancholia, drawing for pictorial title of <emphasis effect="italics">The Sphinx</emphasis>.” Pen and ink on pink paper. 7 5/8 x 5 ½ inches. Present whereabouts unknown. A reproduction of this drawing, which was previously in the collection of Mary Hyde, Viscountess Eccles, was reproduced in <emphasis effect="italics">The Turn of A Century 1885-1910: Art Nouveau – Jugendstil Books</emphasis> (Houghton Library, Harvard University, 1970), p. 18 It is likely that the drawing is currently uncatalogued at the British Library, where the bulk of Lady Eccles’s library went following her death in 2001.</para>
