    <section id="id1166284952433">
      <title>Unsigned parody of The Sphinx [by Ada Leverson and E. T. Reed], published in Punch</title>
      <para id="id1166279624417">An unsigned verbal parody of <emphasis effect="italics">The Sphinx</emphasis> (discussed in the Afterword) by Wilde’s friend Ada Leverson, accompanied by an unsigned caricature of Ricketts’s illustrations by E. T. Reed, published in <emphasis effect="italics">Punch; or</emphasis><emphasis effect="italics">The London Charivari</emphasis>, 21 July 1894, (107), 33. </para>
